34typedef struct dns_master_style dns_master_style_t;
35
36/***
37 *** Definitions
38 ***/
39
40/*
41 * Flags affecting master file formatting. Flags 0x0000FFFF
42 * define the formatting of the rdata part and are defined in
43 * rdata.h.
44 */
45
46/*% Omit the owner name when possible. */
47#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_OMIT_OWNER 0x000010000ULL
48
49/*%
50 * Omit the TTL when possible. If DNS_STYLEFLAG_TTL is
51 * also set, this means no TTLs are ever printed
52 * because $TTL directives are generated before every
53 * change in the TTL. In this case, no columns need to
54 * be reserved for the TTL. Master files generated with
55 * these options will be rejected by BIND 4.x because it
56 * does not recognize the $TTL directive.
57 *
58 * If DNS_STYLEFLAG_TTL is not also set, the TTL will be
59 * omitted when it is equal to the previous TTL.
60 * This is correct according to RFC1035, but the
61 * TTLs may be silently misinterpreted by older
62 * versions of BIND which use the SOA MINTTL as a
63 * default TTL value.
64 */
65#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_OMIT_TTL 0x000020000ULL
66
67/*% Omit the class when possible. */
68#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_OMIT_CLASS 0x000040000ULL
69
70/*% Output $TTL directives. */
71#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_TTL 0x000080000ULL
72
73/*%
74 * Output $ORIGIN directives and print owner names relative to
75 * the origin when possible.
76 */
77#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_REL_OWNER 0x000100000ULL
78
79/*% Print domain names in RR data in relative form when possible.
80 For this to take effect, DNS_STYLEFLAG_REL_OWNER must also be set. */
81#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_REL_DATA 0x000200000ULL
82
83/*% Print the trust level of each rdataset. */
84#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_TRUST 0x000400000ULL
85
86/*% Print negative caching entries. */
87#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_NCACHE 0x000800000ULL
88
89/*% Never print the TTL. */
90#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_NO_TTL 0x001000000ULL
91
92/*% Never print the CLASS. */
93#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_NO_CLASS 0x002000000ULL
94
95/*% Report re-signing time. */
96#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_RESIGN 0x004000000ULL
97
98/*% Don't printout the cryptographic parts of DNSSEC records. */
99#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_NOCRYPTO 0x008000000ULL
100
101/*% Comment out data by prepending with ";" */
102#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_COMMENTDATA 0x010000000ULL
103
104/*% Print TTL with human-readable units. */
105#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_TTL_UNITS 0x020000000ULL
106
107/*% Indent output. */
108#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_INDENT 0x040000000ULL
109
110/*% Output in YAML style. */
111#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_YAML 0x080000000ULL
112
113/*% Print ECS cache entries as comments (reserved for future use). */
114#define DNS_STYLEFLAG_ECSCACHE 0x100000000ULL
115
116ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
117
118/***
119 *** Constants
120 ***/
121
122/*%
123 * The default master file style.
124 *
125 * This uses $TTL directives to avoid the need to dedicate a
126 * tab stop for the TTL. The class is only printed for the first
127 * rrset in the file and shares a tab stop with the RR type.
128 */
129LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_default;
130
131/*%
132 * A master file style that dumps zones to a very generic format easily
133 * imported/checked with external tools.
134 */
135LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_full;
136
137/*%
138 * A master file style that prints explicit TTL values on each
139 * record line, never using $TTL statements. The TTL has a tab
140 * stop of its own, but the class and type share one.
141 */
142LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t
143 dns_master_style_explicitttl;
144
145/*%
146 * A master style format designed for cache files. It prints explicit TTL
147 * values on each record line and never uses $ORIGIN or relative names.
148 */
149LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_cache;
150
151/*%
152 * A master style that prints name, ttl, class, type, and value on
153 * every line. Similar to explicitttl above, but more verbose.
154 * Intended for generating master files which can be easily parsed
155 * by perl scripts and similar applications.
156 */
157LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_simple;
158
159/*%
160 * The style used for debugging, "dig" output, etc.
161 */
162LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_debug;
163
164/*%
165 * Similar to dns_master_style_debug but data is prepended with ";"
166 */
167LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_comment;
168
169/*%
170 * Similar to dns_master_style_debug but data is indented with
171 * dns_master_indentstr (defaults to tab).
172 */
173LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_indent;
174
175/*%
176 * The style used for dumping "key" zones.
177 */
178LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_keyzone;
179
180/*%
181 * YAML-compatible output
182 */
183LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const dns_master_style_t dns_master_style_yaml;
184
185/*%
186 * The default indent string to prepend lines with when using
187 * styleflag DNS_STYLEFLAG_INDENT or DNS_STYLEFLAG_YAML.
188 * This is set to "\t" by default. The indent is repeated
189 * 'dns_master_indent' times. This precedes everything else
190 * on the line, including comment characters (;).
191 *
192 * XXX: Changing this value at runtime is not thread-safe.
193 */
194LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern const char *dns_master_indentstr;
195
196/*%
197 * The number of copies of the indent string to put at the beginning
198 * of the line when using DNS_STYLEFLAG_INDENT or DNS_STYLEFLAG_YAML.
199 * This is set to 1 by default. It is increased and decreased
200 * to adjust indentation levels when producing YAML output.
201 *
202 * XXX: This is not thread-safe.
203 */
204LIBDNS_EXTERNAL_DATA extern unsigned int dns_master_indent;
205

260/*@{*/
261isc_result_t
262dns_master_dumptostreaminc(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_db_t *db,
263 dns_dbversion_t *version,
264 const dns_master_style_t *style, FILE *f,
265 isc_task_t *task, dns_dumpdonefunc_t done,
266 void *done_arg, dns_dumpctx_t **dctxp);
267
268isc_result_t
269dns_master_dumptostream(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_db_t *db,
270 dns_dbversion_t *version,
271 const dns_master_style_t *style,
272 dns_masterformat_t format,
273 dns_masterrawheader_t *header, FILE *f);
274/*%<
275 * Dump the database 'db' to the steam 'f' in the specified format by
276 * 'format'. If the format is dns_masterformat_text (the RFC1035 format),
277 * 'style' specifies the file style (e.g., &dns_master_style_default).
278 *
279 * dns_master_dumptostream() is an old form of dns_master_dumptostream3(),
280 * which always specifies the dns_masterformat_text format.
281 * dns_master_dumptostream2() is an old form which always specifies
282 * a NULL header.
283 *
284 * If 'format' is dns_masterformat_raw, then 'header' can contain
285 * information to be written to the file header.
286 *
287 * Temporary dynamic memory may be allocated from 'mctx'.
288 *
289 * Require:
290 *\li 'task' to be valid.
291 *\li 'done' to be non NULL.
292 *\li 'dctxp' to be non NULL && '*dctxp' to be NULL.
293 *
294 * Returns:
295 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS
296 *\li ISC_R_CONTINUE dns_master_dumptostreaminc() only.
297 *\li ISC_R_NOMEMORY
298 *\li Any database or rrset iterator error.
299 *\li Any dns_rdata_totext() error code.
300 */
301/*@}*/
302
303/*@{*/
304
305isc_result_t
306dns_master_dumpinc(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *version,
307 const dns_master_style_t *style, const char *filename,
308 isc_task_t *task, dns_dumpdonefunc_t done, void
309 *done_arg, dns_dumpctx_t **dctxp,
310 dns_masterformat_t format, dns_masterrawheader_t *header);
311
312isc_result_t
313dns_master_dump(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_db_t *db,
314 dns_dbversion_t *version,
315 const dns_master_style_t *style, const char *filename,
316 dns_masterformat_t format, dns_masterrawheader_t *header);
317
318/*%<
319 * Dump the database 'db' to the file 'filename' in the specified format by
320 * 'format'. If the format is dns_masterformat_text (the RFC1035 format),
321 * 'style' specifies the file style (e.g., &dns_master_style_default).
322 *
323 * dns_master_dumpinc() and dns_master_dump() are old forms of _dumpinc3()
324 * and _dump3(), respectively, which always specify the dns_masterformat_text
325 * format. dns_master_dumpinc2() and dns_master_dump2() are old forms which
326 * always specify a NULL header.
327 *
328 * If 'format' is dns_masterformat_raw, then 'header' can contain
329 * information to be written to the file header.
330 *
331 * Temporary dynamic memory may be allocated from 'mctx'.
332 *
333 * Returns:
334 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS
335 *\li ISC_R_CONTINUE dns_master_dumpinc() only.
336 *\li ISC_R_NOMEMORY
337 *\li Any database or rrset iterator error.
338 *\li Any dns_rdata_totext() error code.
339 */
340/*@}*/
341
342isc_result_t
343dns_master_rdatasettotext(const dns_name_t *owner_name,
344 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
345 const dns_master_style_t *style,
346 isc_buffer_t *target);
347/*%<
348 * Convert 'rdataset' to text format, storing the result in 'target'.
349 *
350 * Notes:
351 *\li The rdata cursor position will be changed.
352 *
353 * Requires:
354 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid non-question rdataset.
355 *
356 *\li 'rdataset' is not empty.
357 */
358
359isc_result_t
360dns_master_questiontotext(const dns_name_t *owner_name,
361 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
362 const dns_master_style_t *style,
363 isc_buffer_t *target);
